ADDITIONAL NOTICE — ORIGINAL AUTHORSHIP AND DEVELOPMENT LINEAGE
This repository represents original independent research by Catherine Earl, developed from first principles as foundational work in the development of quantum hybrid inference methodology subsequently implemented under OmniHenos Ltd (2023–present).
The Clifford algebra compression pipeline, zero-dependency C++ diffusion architecture, custom Adam optimiser implementation, BPE tokenisation pipeline, and Gaussian diffusion training loop contained herein constitute original research work predating and informing proprietary systems under active IP protection.
Timestamped authorship is established via GitHub commit history and development documentation. This repository forms part of a documented research lineage connecting classical diffusion methodology to quantum hybrid inference architecture.
Unauthorised commercial use, reproduction, or appropriation of this framework, its architecture, or its methodology — in whole or in part — without explicit written permission from the author will be pursued.

